\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 cups uncooked elbow macaroni (an 8-ounce box isn't quite 2 cups)\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 tablespoons (1/2 stuck) butter, cut into pieces\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 1/2 cups (about 10 ounces) grated sharp {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cheddar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Cheddar cheese}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 eggs, beaten\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sour-cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 sour cream}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 (10 3/4-ounce) can condensed Cheddar cheese soup\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup whole milk\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon dry {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mustard/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mustard}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon black pepper\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Boil the macaroni in a 2 quart {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}} in plenty of water until tender, about 7 minutes. Drain. In a medium saucepan, mix butter and cheese. Stir until the cheese melts. In a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/slow-cooker/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 slow cooker}}, combine cheese/{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/butter/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 butter}} mixture and add the eggs, sour cream, soup, salt, milk, mustard and pepper and stir well. Then add drained {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/macaroni/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 macaroni}} and stir again. Set the slow cooker on low setting and cook for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.\
